            <p class="uk-text-large">This website was created to fulfill the capstone requirements for an ALM degree from the Harvard Extension School’s Digital Media Design program. The real impetus for this project, however, stems from my personal passion for the wine-tasting hobby and my continual enjoyment of discovering new wines from great wine-makers in Southeastern Washington. My name is Justin Myre, the sole creator and developer of Tri-Cities Wine Hub, and I chose to create this website to fill a void I found on the internet when it comes to tasting wine in the Tri-Cities area, which just so happens to be my hometown. My primary goal was to create a community-focused, feature-rich dynamic web application for not only wine enthusiasts who call Tri-Cities their home but also for those who visit us from abroad. It is my sincerest hope that Tri-Cities Wine Hub can address our wine community’s lack of internet presence for what is otherwise a burgeoning and robust wine region.</p>

			<p class="uk-text-large">Tri-Cities Wine Hub is not intended to just be an informational website about wine or a place where users can rate wines and wineries, but I find that it has the potential to impact the wine tourism and tasting industry in the Tri-Cities by creating a community platform for users who regularly participate or want to participate in regional wine tasting. Although there are many wine tasting applications that Tri-Cities wine enthusiasts can use, and there are easily accessible resources that provide information about the region’s wines and wineries, nothing truly exists as a “hub” to bring all these elements together for this specific wine region in a simplified, cohesive production.  By utilizing a streamlined user interface, Tri-Cities Wine Hub can be the go-to website application for both local and visiting wine tourists who prefer to have all of these application features and informational resources in one website.</p> 

